                <h2 class="helvetica"> How to Take Care of Your Cat</h2>
    
                <p class="helvetica">
                    Taking care of a cat is crucial for their well-being and happiness.
                    Cats rely on their owners for basic needs such as food, water, shelter,
                    and medical care. Proper care also includes providing mental
                    stimulation through play, ensuring they have a clean and safe
                    environment, and offering affection and companionship.
                    A well-cared-for cat is more likely to be healthy, exhibit fewer
                    behavioral issues, and form a strong, trusting bond with its owner.
                    By attending to a cat's needs, owners contribute to the overall quality
                    of life for their feline friend, fostering a loving and rewarding
                    relationship.
                </p>
    
                <div class="helvetica-3">
                    <ol>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Regular Vet Check-Ups:</span> 
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Schedule routine veterinary visits for vaccinations and overall health assessments.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Balanced Diet:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Feed your cat a nutritious diet appropriate for their age, health, and activity level.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Fresh Water:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Ensure your cat always has access to fresh, clean water.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Litter Box Maintenance:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Keep the litter box clean and place it in a quiet, easily accessible location.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Grooming:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Regularly brush your cat to reduce shedding and prevent matting.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Play and Exercise:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Provide toys and interactive playtime to keep your cat mentally and physically stimulated.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Scratching Posts:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Offer scratching posts or pads to help your cat maintain healthy claws and avoid furniture damage.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Safe Environment:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Make sure your home is safe, with no hazardous substances or items your cat could ingest or get hurt by.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Affection and Socialization:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Spend quality time with your cat to build a strong bond and ensure they feel loved and secure.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Monitor Behavior:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Pay attention to any changes in your cat's behavior or habits, as these can indicate health issues that may need veterinary attention.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
